import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

In [19]:
def sawtooth(sr, duration, f0, n_harmonics = 11):
    t = np.arange(int(duration*sr))/sr
    y = np.zeros_like(t)
    for i in range(1, n_harmonics):
        y -= np.sin(2*np.pi*(f0*i)*t)/i
    return y

def square(sr, duration, f0, n_harmonics = 11):
    t = np.arange(int(duration*sr))/sr
    y = np.zeros_like(t)
    a = 1.0
    for i in range(1, n_harmonics):
        if i%2 == 1:
            y += a*np.cos(2*np.pi*(f0*i)*t)/i
            a *= -1
    return y

def triangle(sr, duration, f0, n_harmonics = 11):
    t = np.arange(int(duration*sr))/sr
    y = np.zeros_like(t)
    a = 1.0
    for i in range(1, 21):
        if i%2 == 1:
            y += a*np.sin(2*np.pi*(f0*i)*t)/(i**2)
            a *= -1
    return y

def chromatic(N, sr, duration, fn_waveform):
    """
    Parameters
    ----------
    N: int
        How many halfsteps to go up, starting at concert A
    sr: int
        Sample rate
    duration: float
        Lenth of each note (in seconds)
    fn_waveform: function: (sr, duration, f0) -> numpy array of a note
        Generate a waveform for a particular note
    """
    y = np.array([])
    for p in range(N):
        f0 = 440*(2**(p/12))
        y_p = fn_waveform(sr, duration, f0)
        y = np.concatenate((y, y_p))
    return y

sr = 44100
fn_waveform = lambda sr, duration, f0: square(sr, duration, f0, 21)
y = chromatic(12, sr, 0.5, fn_waveform)
ipd.Audio(y, rate=sr)
